ue for a use of datalad-installer to actually install datalad itself.\r\n\r\nBut I wondered if we should may be still \"have\" it as a core dependency and add that `datalad.install`?  That should simplify at least installation of datalad on osx and windows, where we could do \"install datalad\" (conda, pip, etc; conda would need to have it packaged) + `python -m datalad.install git-annex`.  That could also be accomplished via \"install datalad-installer\" + `python -m datalad_installer git-annex datalad` and that is why I am a bit luke warm about it...\r\n\r\nWDYT @datalad/developers ?", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5378/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5378/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}